<CENTER><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>The First Epistle of Paul to the Thessalonians</H2>    
</CENTER><P><A HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 
CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 5</H1></CENTER>    
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>But of the times  
and the seasons, brethren, ye have no need that I write unto you.</P></TD></TR> 
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>For yourselves know         
perfectly that the day of the ADONAY so cometh as a thief in the night.</P></TD>
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>For when they shall    
say, Peace and safety; then sudden destruction cometh upon them, as travail     
upon a woman with child; and they shall not escape.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD        
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>But ye, brethren, are not in        
darkness, that that day should overtake you as a thief.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD    
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>Ye are all the children of light,   
and the children of the day: we are not of the night, nor of darkness.</P></TD> 
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>Therefore let us not   
sleep, as do others; but let us watch and be sober.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD        
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>For they that sleep sleep in the    
night; and they that be drunken are drunken in the night.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD  
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>But let us, who are of the day, be  
sober, putting on the breastplate of faith and love; and for an helmet, the     
hope of salvation.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>For ELOHIYM hath not appointed us to wrath, but to obtain salvation by   
our ADONAY YAHSHUA MASHIYACH,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>  
10</H4></TD><TD><P>Who died for us, that, whether we wake or sleep, we should   
live together with him.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4> 
</TD><TD><P>Wherefore comfort yourselves together, and edify one another, even  
as also ye do.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD> 
<P>And we beseech you, brethren, to know them which labour among you, and are   
over you in the ADONAY, and admonish you;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>And to esteem them very highly in love for      
their work's sake. And be at peace among yourselves.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD       
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>Now we exhort you, brethren, warn 
them that are unruly, comfort the feebleminded, support the weak, be patient    
toward all men.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD>
<P>See that none render evil for evil unto any man; but ever follow that which  
is good, both among yourselves, and to all men.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>
<A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>Rejoice evermore.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD       
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>Pray without ceasing.</P></TD>    
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>In every thing give  
thanks: for this is the will of ELOHIYM in MASHIYACH YAHSHUA concerning you.</P>
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>Quench not the  
Spirit.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>     
Despise not prophesyings.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V21><H4>      
21</H4></TD><TD><P>Prove all things; hold fast that which is good.</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>22</H4></TD><TD><P>Abstain from all          
appearance of evil.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V23><H4>23</H4></TD>
<TD><P>And the very EL of peace sanctify you wholly; and I pray your whole      
spirit and soul and body be preserved blameless unto the coming of our ADONAY   
YAHSHUA MASHIYACH.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V24><H4>24</H4></TD> 
<TD><P>Faithful is he that calleth you, who also will do it.</P></TD></TR><TR>  
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V25><H4>25</H4></TD><TD><P>Brethren, pray for us.</P>    
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V26><H4>26</H4></TD><TD><P>Greet all the   
brethren with an holy kiss.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V27><H4>    
27</H4></TD><TD><P>I charge you by the ADONAY that this epistle be read unto    
all the holy brethren.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V28><H4>28</H4>  
</TD><TD><P>The grace of our ADONAY YAHSHUA MASHIYACH be with you. Amen.</P>    
